The paper discusses a metric for measuring the impact of research papers, which is relevant to several sub-fields of computer science. However, the focus on publication years and citation frequencies suggests a stronger connection to sub-fields such as digital libraries (cs.DL), information retrieval (cs.IR), machine learning (cs.LG), social and information networks (cs.SI), and databases (cs.DB).
